HEADWORD: grouchy
<hw>grouch"y</hw> <pr>(grouch"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>adj.</pos> <def>given to
complaining or grumbling; prone to show annoyance at slight provocation;
irritable.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> crabbed, crabby, cross, fussy, fussbudgety, grumpy,
bad-tempered, ill-tempered.</syn>⟦br⟧
